 File: `man_1_simple_shell`

```man
.TH HSH 1 "December 2025" "Holberton School" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a simple UNIX command interpreter written in C.
It executes commands entered by the user or read from standard input.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.IP
./hsh

Non-interactive mode:
.IP
echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell uses the PATH environment variable to locate executable files.

.SH EXIT STATUS
hsh exits with status 0 on success, and non-zero on error.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1)

.SH AUTHOR
James Roussel and Maxime RÃ©gnier, Holberton School students.
